[b]Market Stress Oscillator[/b] is a bi-directional Williams VIX Fix based stress indicator — measuring both downside and upside stress — filtered with JMA smoothing and ADX, with peak-hold event markers to highlight stress extremes.

[b]What it does[/b]

The Williams VIX Fix approximates the VIX from price data by measuring how far the current close is from the highest high over a lookback window. This script extends the concept bidirectionally — tracking both bearish stress (downside panic) and bullish stress (upside frenzy) — and uses JMA and ADX filters to separate meaningful stress events from noise. Peak-hold markers flag bars where stress reached a local extreme.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Bi-directional WVF[/b] — Separate bull and bear stress lines on a single oscillator panel
[*][b]JMA smoothing[/b] — Jurik Moving Average applied to reduce noise on both series
[*][b]ADX filter[/b] — Optionally suppresses signals when trend strength is too low (ranging conditions)
[*][b]Peak-hold event markers[/b] — Flags stress spikes that exceed a configurable threshold
[/list]

